Djibouti’s Police Chief Injured After Being Shot by Officer

-- B y   M o h a m e d   O s m a n   F a r a h
-- 
2011-09-30T05:57:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-30/djibouti-s-police-chief-injured-after-being-shot-by-officer.html
A Djiboutian policeman shot and
injured Police Chief Colonel Abdillahi Abdi Farah in an attack
at his office, Interior Minister Hassan Darar Houffaneh said.  Farah was shot in the head and is being treated at the
Bouffard Hospital, a French military facility, in the capital,
Djibouti City, Houffaneh said in a phone interview yesterday.
The attacker, a non-commissioned police officer, was arrested
and is being questioned, he said.  The motive of the attack hasn’t been established yet,
Houffaneh said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mohamed Osman Farah in Djibouti via Nairobi at   pmrichardson@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Paul Richardson  at 
